<headline>Special Weather Statement issued February 05 at 5:08PM MST  by NWS GreatFalls</headline>
<description>...Slow moving band of snow to impact portions of North Central
and Central Montana into early evening hours...
At 5 pm, the band of light to moderate snow showers continues to
stretch from near Cut Bank southeast through western Chouteau
County, Judith Basin County, and southwest Fergus County, moving
slowly to the southwest. Although radar indicates that the middle
section of this line is weakening, it may still bring some light
snow showers to the Great Falls area by 7 pm.
Additional accumulation should remain less than one inch, but
visibility may be reduced below one mile at times and some roads
may become icy.
Use caution while driving through these areas, and be prepared for
rapidly changing weather and road conditions.</description>
